==English==
===Etymology===
from Latin ''quinquagesima dies'' (50th day)

===Noun===
'''Quinquagesima'''
# (''Christian'') a [[Sunday]] in the [[Christian]] [[calendar]]. It is 50 days, using [[inclusively counting]], backwards, from [[Easter]] Sunday.

